  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b1c3cae70ad8d9641a4b5be915b33736, type: 3}
  m_Name: Lamp3_long3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  lines:
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 21300000, guid: f37d4b9411651a245acd90381f07228a, type: 3}
    text: But then this guy just threw the lamp into the river. Like, just threw
      it. No warning, no reason, no speech, nothing. I was like, okay, that was rude.
      I did not know that lamp personally, but still, as another lamp, I felt something.
      Maybe sadness. Maybe secondhand embarrassment.
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 21300000, guid: a6690421363fada43a0a73ded1a1f6a9, type: 3}
    text: And then, almost immediately, this random old guy came out of the water.
      Very dramatic. Very wet. Very shiny. I thought he was going to pick up the
      lamp that just got thrown in, because that would make sense, right? But no.
      He looked around for one second and grabbed me.
  options:
  - speakerName: You
    portrait: {fileID: 21300000, guid: c94401dbaeda7ba41b8f6b821553714a, type: 3}
    replyText: ............
    nextNode: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 770aa17a7bf2c89419f7d7c9053da33c, type: 2}
  - speakerName: You
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    replyText: Stop. I changed my mind. Give me the short version.
    nextNode: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7034a0dadb3a5684698faa0db94ee5aa, type: 2}
